cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with energy-efficient transmission protocols for wireless networks, specifically for device-to-device communication. It focuses on the opportunistic approach, which selects a single neighboring device as a relay to minimize energy consumption. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves analytical bounds and scaling laws, indicating a possibility of cs.IT (Information Theory). Moreover, the study of energy efficiency in wireless networks can be related to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the simulations in realistic scenarios suggest a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia).
